cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.QL, cs.LO, cs.PL 

The paper discusses a novel and quantum cost efficient reversible full adder gate in nanotechnology. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Emerging Technologies (cs.ET) as it deals with a new technology. Additionally, the paper also mentions the gate's applications in cryptography, which falls under the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and the gate's adherence to theoretical minimum, which falls under the sub-category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The gate's use in synthesizing arbitrary Boolean functions suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Programming Languages (cs.PL). Finally, the mention of quantum cost efficiency suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of Quantum Computing (cs.QL).
